Rename #config.js to config.js (remove the # sign)
Open config.js and replace the "YourUserHere" text with your steam username, and "YourPasshere" with your steam password. 
Your username and password must be written INSIDE the " " marks containing name and pass.

Now to start the script:

1. Install Docker Engine OR Docker desktop
2. when located in the folder where files are located, run this command:
docker build -t steam-friend-deny .

That will build the docker "image" but the script is not yet running, to run the script run command: docker run -it steam-friend-deny

This will run the container